## **Accessing Cases**

1. Log in to DDMx, select the 9 dots and go to **‚ÄúCase Management‚Äù**

**![][image2]**

## **Queue View**

1. [\[Arcgate\] Comm Ops Request Cases](https://doordashmx.lightning.force.com/lightning/o/Case/list?filterName=00BPg000003OVgrMAG)  
2. The list view will contain all \[Arcgate\] Comm Ops cases![][image3]

## **Case Priority**

1. If Status \= ESCALATED, claim those first  
2. If Rank \= 10+, priortize after escalated cases  
3. Oldest created case (FIFO \- First In, First Out)  
   1. For Status \= BLOCKED, review Case Comment for responses   
      1. If response available, complete request  
      2. If no response, send follow-up message:  
         1. *Friendly bump\! Just checking in on my previous message‚Äîlet me know if you have any updates or need any clarification. Thanks\!*

## **Claiming a Case**

1. To take ownership, check the boxes next to the cases you want to assign to yourself and select ‚ÄúChange Owner‚Äù at the top of the list.  
2. Once assigned, change the status to ‚ÄúIn Progress‚Äù.

## **Updating Case Status**

* In Progress: Actively working on the case  
* Escalated: Waiting on guidance.  
* Blocked: Waiting on a response from the rep. Bump blocked cases with reps every other day with a friendly reminder. If the requester does not respond after one business day, add a comment: "*Friendly bump\! Just checking in on my previous message‚Äîlet me know if you have any updates or need any clarification. Thanks*\!"  
* Closed: No further action required from Comm Ops. Select from:  
  * Completed: Issue resolved by Comm Ops.  
  * No Response from AO: No response or activity from the AO ‚Äì  close if no response after 3 days  
  * Not Required Anymore: Issue cancelled or resolved by another team.  
  * Not Comm Ops Related: Incorrectly submitted case, no action required.  
  * Other: Provide reasoning for closing the case.

## **Communicating with a Requester**

* If additional information is needed, submit a new ‚ÄúCase Comments‚Äù at the bottom of the page.  
  * Add updates, questions, or comments for the requester.

## **Adding Internal Notes to a Case**

1. Navigate to the "Notes and Attachments" tab.  
2. Under "Notes", select "New" to add notes. Use notes to track progress and add context for anyone reviewing the case.

   ## **üõ†Ô∏è SFDC Case Closure Guide**

   ### **üìå When to Use:**

Use this guide when you are ready to **close** a case that has been fully resolved and work is complete.

---

### **‚úÖ Step-by-Step Closure Process**

1. **Set Status to**: `Closed`  
2. **Closed Category**: 

| Closed Category | Additional Text Box | Reason for Use |
| ----- | ----- | ----- |
| **Training / Self-Serve** | N/A | Used when reps submit a request that already has a documented **self-serve process** available. Helps track gaps in training or knowledge. |
| **Data Issue** | N/A | Used when Comm Ops resolves a **data discrepancy** (e.g., deck rank, account owner update, account setup correction). |
| **System Error / Bug** | Ticket link (if applicable) \- use existing JIRA\_Ticket\_\_c | Used when updates are needed due to a **system error, limitation, or bug**. Linking the Jira/ServiceNow ticket provides traceability. |
| **Hand-Off** | Required field to specify team/channel |  Used when Comm Ops must **redirect the request** to another team‚Äôs owned process (e.g., Sales Ops, Legal, Support). Ensures accountability and routing visibility. |
| **Compliance** | N/A | Used for assisting reps with valid **compliance-related requests** (e.g., policy adherence, regulatory requirements). |
| **Duplicate** | N/A | Used when the case is a **duplicate submission** and has already been addressed. |

3. **Set Sub-Status to**: `Completed`

4. **Enter Story Points**

   * Assign **1 story point per completed action or scenario** within the case.

   * Each investigation or deep dive also counts as **1 story point**.

   * Use this to quantify effort, not just resolution.

5. **Fill in ‚ÄúAdditional Case Comments‚Äù**

## **Area: Amendment / Quoting \> Type: Churned Mx**

### **Churned Mx**

These case requests will consist of identifying and correcting Churned SMB Mx in DDMx.

| Steps to Follow: Step 1: Identify Incorrectly Migrated Churned Mx Claim \+ Open case Set Status to In Progress Navigate to the contract on the case Navigate to the Store account in question on the contract linked via Agreement. Check Store Status: Click on the store record. Verify the status field is marked "Inactive" or "Deactivated". Pull up the store in Mint and verify the store is truly Inactive If the store is live in Mint, then you will need to block the case and add a case comment, ‚ÄúHi, we are only able to churn Inactive stores. Please ensure the store is showing fully permanently deactivated in Mint prior to submitting a churn case.‚Äù Once the rep has deactivated the store double-check in Mint and proceed to updating the contract if deactivated. ![][image22] ![][image23] Step 2: Correct Onboarding for Churned Mx Locate Old Contract: Open the contract provided on the case. Update Order Type: ![][image24]Click the Order link from the old contract. Navigate to the Details Tab. ![][image25] If the Order is in ‚ÄúDraft‚Äù status and not ‚ÄúActivated,‚Äù you will need to click the ‚ÄúChange Status Button.‚Äù Click the button![][image26] Update the status from Draft to Activated![][image27]   Proceed to next step ![][image28] Click on the Order Type. ![][image29]Edit Order Type to "Churned Mx". Click Save. Step 3: Close out the case Go back to the Comm Ops case and click the Close Case button![][image7] Set the Sub Status to Completed Add Additional Case Comments ‚ÄúHello I got the contact marked as churn. DDMx has a system update that runs at 8 am, 12 pm, 4 pm (etc.) PST, after the system will update all records associated with the churned contract to the correct status (delete Store Agreements and Services with the older contract, mark the work orders as ‚ÄòDead‚Äô, and mark the xref as inactive for all the associated store accounts). ## **Area: Work Order Not Started \> Type: Address Verification Escalation**

These case requests will consist of internal members needing assistance for updates in **Area \=  Work Order Not Started** and **Type \= Address Verification Escalation**

### **Address Verification**

The requester is reaching out to verify the Store or Business Account‚Äôs address inside of DDMX

* **NOTE**: If the request Description does not fall into this category, please follow the [Escalation Path to Commercial Operations](#bookmark=id.6peikl6ctdq3)

**Steps to Follow:**

1. Claim \+ Open case  
2. Review the **Description** for exact details on the account address that is needing to be verified. Often time reps will also attach the store account and address to the left side in the **Address Verification Request Information** section  
3. Navigate to the account page linked in the **Address Verification Request Information** section or the account provided in the **Description. (**Note: if the rep doesn‚Äôt provide you with enough information (either a linked store/business account or an address) to proceed feel free to leave a case comment saying ‚Äú*Please provide the link to the account that is experiencing the issue so that I may best assist here\! Thank you*\!‚Äù and then block the case until the correct information is provided. 

![][image43]

4. First check the **Coverage** section at the top.   
   * If this says **In Coverage** please continue to step 6  
   * If this says **Not in Coverage** or is **Blank** please continue to step 5

![][image44]

5. Navigate down to the account‚Äôs **Address Information** section and copy the address listed  
   * Go to the Map Manager tool here [https://admin-gateway.doordash.com/tools/geo\_tools/map\_manager](https://admin-gateway.doordash.com/tools/geo_tools/map_manager) and input the address in the **Location Finder** search field

![][image45]

* A pin with a house should appear at that address showing the exact location of the account. ![][image46]If the pin is showing inside of a blue square/area, then go back to the account inside of DDMX and hit the **Verify Address** button. This should change the coverage message to **In Coverage (Proceed to Step 6\)**

![][image47]

* If the pin is showing outside of a blue square/area then the address is not inside a DoorDash Starting Point and the coverage will need to be expanded.   
  * In this instance you can tell the rep ‚Äú*Unfortunately this address is outside of a starting point and is currently out of coverage. The \#so-launch team handles starting point expansion requests and you can request an expansion using this google form \- [https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSffNm7Gu\_kFzcSdA9-pfyZbxtBXI6I61vX32R47FOMIHC4nZA/viewform](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSffNm7Gu_kFzcSdA9-pfyZbxtBXI6I61vX32R47FOMIHC4nZA/viewform) . Once submitted you can track the progress of your request here \- [https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1RrTB8pLXPCWbHecSZO8hXOMxw8Rhu9I81qFuhXnqkqA/edit?resourcekey=\&gid=258936605\#gid=258936605](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1RrTB8pLXPCWbHecSZO8hXOMxw8Rhu9I81qFuhXnqkqA/edit?resourcekey=&gid=258936605#gid=258936605) . Thank you and have a nice day\!*‚Äù and close out the case. 

![][image48]

6. Navigate down to the account‚Äôs **Address Information** section and review the **Coverage** and **Address Verification Status** fields. **Coverage** should say **In Coverage**  
   * If **Address Verification Status** says **Verified**, please continue to Step 8   
   * If **Address Verification Status** says **Unverified** or **Rejected**, please continue to Step 7

     

![][image49]

7. Copy the address listed and go to **Google Maps**. Type the **name** of the account and paste the **address** inside of **Google Maps** to find the location.   
   * Once you‚Äôve found the location in **Google Maps**, right click the pin and click on the **lat/long coordinates** that populate at the top. This will copy the coordinates for you. 

![][image50]

* Once the coordinates are copied, navigate to Atlas [https://unity.doordash.com/suites/geo/atlas](https://unity.doordash.com/suites/geo/atlas) and paste the coordinates in the search field

![][image51]

#### Nearby Pins 

##### If there are no pins at or near your location scroll down to the ‚ÄúNo Nearby Pins‚Äù section

* You will see a **green pin (User Provided Point)** and potentially other **blue pins (verified existing addresses in DDMX)**. If there is a blue pin that is very close to your provided pin and/or it shares the same address as the account does you can click on that pin (**it will then turn red**) and you can copy the **Source Place Id.**

**![][image52]**

**![][image53]**

* With the **Source Place Id** copied, you can navigate back to the account in DDMX and scroll down to the **Address Information** section. Click the **pencil** to edit the address, **remove all the information from the Street field**, and paste the **Source Place Id in the street field and save**. 

![][image54]

* Navigate back up to the top of the account page and hit the **Verify Address** button. If it says the address is already verified you should be fine to just refresh the page and then recheck the **Address Information** section and see **Coverage** showing as **In Coverage** and **Address Verification Status** showing as **Verified**.

![][image47]

8. Once the account is appearing as In Coverage and Verified you can leave a comment to the rep stating ‚Äú*The account is now appearing as In Coverage and Verified. You should be all set to proceed. Thank you and have a nice day.*‚Äù and close out the case. 

#### No Nearby Pins 

* If there are no nearby pins that means that the address is currently missing in DDMX and will need to be requested to be added. In this scenario you can use the message ‚Äú*Hello\! This case is being escalated internally. If this is a P0 request, please use the Senior Manager Escalations process to ensure they‚Äôre handled promptly. Thanks in advance for your understanding\! [https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1a-nXry31R4328nSNCuO-XqrwTBzw7L1LQJ2iExPF7SU/edit?gid=608455224\#gid=608455224](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1a-nXry31R4328nSNCuO-XqrwTBzw7L1LQJ2iExPF7SU/edit?gid=608455224#gid=608455224)*‚Äù and then escalate the case to Comm Ops
